{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_f354b815b0144f9c93681f8e","type":"tool_result","content":"85\t\n86\tclass Guard(IGuard, Generic[OT]):\n87\t    \"\"\"The Guard class.\n88\t\n89\t    This class is the main entry point for using Guardrails. It can be\n90\t    initialized by one of the following patterns:\n91\t\n92\t    - `Guard().use(...)`\n93\t    - `Guard.for_string(...)`\n94\t    - `Guard.for_pydantic(...)`\n95\t    - `Guard.for_rail(...)`\n96\t    - `Guard.for_rail_string(...)`\n97\t\n98\t    The `__call__`\n99\t    method functions as a wrapper around LLM APIs. It takes in an LLM\n100\t    API, and optional prompt parameters, and returns a ValidationOutcome\n101\t    class that contains the raw output from\n102\t    the LLM, the validated output, as well as other helpful information.\n103\t    \"\"\"\n104\t\n105\t    history: Stack[Call]\n106\t    _history_max_length: int\n107\t    _use_server: bool\n108\t\n109\t    # Pydantic Config\n110\t    model_config = ConfigDict(arbitrary_types_allowed=True)\n111\t\n112\t    def __init__(\n113\t        self,\n114\t        *,\n115\t        id: Optional[str] = None,\n116\t        name: Optional[str] = None,\n117\t        description: Optional[str] = None,\n118\t        validators: Optional[List[ValidatorReference]] = None,\n119\t        output_schema: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n120\t        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n121\t        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n122\t        history_max_length: Optional[int] = None,\n123\t        use_server: Optional[bool] = None,\n124\t    ):\n125\t        \"\"\"Initialize the Guard with serialized validator references and an\n126\t        output schema.\n127\t\n128\t        Output schema must be a valid JSON Schema.\n129\t        \"\"\"\n130\t        # Shared Interface Properties\n131\t        id = id or str(uuid.uuid4())\n132\t        name = name or f\"gr-{id}\"\n133\t\n134\t        # Defaults"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"